  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
    <subfield code="a">Properties of scalar fields in Rindler and de Sitter spaces are the subject of this work. Using the "brick wall model" the dispersion relations are determined and the remarkable properties common to both spaces as well as their differences are discussed. Equipped with these tools the horizon induced thermodynamics is revisited and shown to be dominated by a single mode propagating perpendicular to the horizon. Explicit expressions for the partition function, entropy and heat capacity for massless and massive fields are presented.</subfield>
  </datafield>
